    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It's not a bad idea, but it's also not great and should have more thought put into it. In a nut shell we should not require an \"[everything is okay alarm](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aJFyWBLeM7Q)\" .\r\n\r\nWhile I agree these technical details should be (and are) available to more advanced users. It's abit regressive to show all them all the time. Our ultimate users shouldn't need to know or worry too much about blockchain. We should declutter and fade as much information into the background. . Only be notified when something is wrong, and do our best to auto-recover for them.\r\n\r\nIn spirit that's what I like about macOS, for new users, all they see is \"shiny\" but for power users they can get under the hood and open a terminal.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
